{"name":"Cosmopolitan","type":"heritage","img":"icons/environment/settlement/palast.webp","system":{"traits":[{"id":"Dflhn6ld7v4uFA4x","name":"Street Smarts","img":"icons/environment/settlement/house-city.webp","description":"While in a city or other urban environment, you and your group can’t become lost except by magical means. While you are in such environments, you also can’t be surprised, except when you are asleep or otherwise incapacitated.","builderInfo":{},"innate":{"proficiencies":[],"languages":[],"resistances":[],"saveAdvantages":[]}},{"id":"QqyI4XNTJoiCxgsx","name":"Worldly Wisdom","img":"icons/environment/people/group.webp","description":"Whenever you make a check related to understanding the purpose or significance of a building, rite, or object from a culture you aren’t familiar with, you can add your PB to the roll. If you have Proficiency in a relevant skill or tool, you add double your PB to the roll.","builderInfo":{},"innate":{"proficiencies":[],"languages":[],"resistances":[],"saveAdvantages":[]}},{"id":"Sr6sUeonBuZhrlHB","name":"Languages","img":"icons/tools/scribal/ink-quill-pink.webp","description":"You know Common and two additional languages of your choice. Typical creatures of this heritage would choose Dwarvish and Elvish.","builderInfo":{},"innate":{"proficiencies":[],"languages":["common"],"resistances":[],"saveAdvantages":[]}}],"alignment":"Choose one of the alignments approved by your GM. Typical creatures of this heritage tend towards Chaotic or Good alignments.","description":"<p>Characters who choose this heritage are citizens of the world whose values, interests, and ideas are influenced by exposure to many different types of peoples and cultures Most commonly creatures of this heritage hail from major cities populated by people from many different parts of the world. Alternatively, it could mean you spent your formative years moving from place to place, immersing yourself in the unique customs and traditions of each community you lived with.</p>"},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.opeAYFTlZnUDukt5"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"black-flag","systemVersion":"This is auto replaced","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1676327219979,"modifiedTime":1676391800178,"lastModifiedBy":"HpJB4dX5ajFbAjnW"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"HpJB4dX5ajFbAjnW":3},"_id":"CH2Yc0sZJe99hVKm"}
{"name":"Nomadic","type":"heritage","img":"icons/environment/wilderness/terrain-river-road-gray.webp","system":{"traits":[{"id":"a4L5ziGOzWYSWss5","name":"Resilient","img":"icons/environment/wilderness/cave-entrance-rocky.webp","description":"You have advantage on checks or saves made to resist debilitating weather effects, such as those caused by extreme heat or cold. Additionally, when you complete a short rest, you can reduce your exhaustion level by one. Once used, you cannot reduce your exhaustion level in this way again until you complete a long rest.","builderInfo":{},"innate":{"proficiencies":[],"languages":[],"resistances":[],"saveAdvantages":[]}},{"id":"AM1kH3tm3Iv9nj5V","name":"Traveler","img":"icons/tools/navigation/map-plain-green.webp","description":"You have Proficiency in the Survival skill.","builderInfo":{},"innate":{"proficiencies":["survival"],"languages":[],"resistances":[],"saveAdvantages":[]}},{"id":"B9HhssbVqBW9I4j6","name":"Languages","img":"icons/tools/scribal/ink-quill-pink.webp","description":"You know Common and one additional language of your choice. Depending on the regions your people frequent or the kinds of communities your people trade with, a typical nomadic character would choose Typical creatures of this heritage would choose Dwarvish or Elvish.","builderInfo":{},"innate":{"proficiencies":[],"languages":["common"],"resistances":[],"saveAdvantages":[]}}],"alignment":"Choose one of the alignments approved by your GM. Typical creatures of this heritage tend towards Neutral or Lawful alignments.","description":"<p>Characters who choose this heritage hail from a tight-knit community that does not live continually in the same place, but regularly moves to and from different areas. Your people may do so to follow seasonally available plants and game, follow established trade routes, or for a more unique reason. Whatever the case, people of nomadic heritage are well suited to the rigors of travel and often possess an intuitive understanding of environmental cycles and the hazards or benefits that come with them.</p>"},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.UJfoCX0CUzma4TOM"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"black-flag","systemVersion":"This is auto replaced","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1676327219979,"modifiedTime":1676391803423,"lastModifiedBy":"HpJB4dX5ajFbAjnW"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"HpJB4dX5ajFbAjnW":3},"_id":"F8ywQFerQ4tjuy8u"}
{"name":"Stone","type":"heritage","img":"icons/magic/earth/construct-stone.webp","system":{"traits":[{"id":"mlPhgBhrOJE1Q7J4","name":"Dwarven Weapon Training","img":"icons/skills/melee/hand-grip-axe-strike-orange.webp","description":"You have Proficiency with the battleaxe, handaxe, light hammer, and warhammer.","builderInfo":{},"innate":{"proficiencies":["battleaxe","handaxe","lightHammer","warhammer"],"languages":[],"resistances":[],"saveAdvantages":[]}},{"id":"lOzz8UNJ3uVHBmm6","name":"Dwarven Armor Training","img":"icons/environment/people/infantry-armored.webp","description":"You have Proficiency with light and medium armor. Additionally, your speed is not reduced by wearing heavy armor—regardless of your STR score.","builderInfo":{},"innate":{"proficiencies":["light","medium"],"languages":[],"resistances":[],"saveAdvantages":[]}},{"id":"Vjbmdpqdfcbe88oh","name":"Tool Proficiency","img":"icons/skills/trades/construction-mason-stonecutter-sculpture.webp","description":"You gain Proficiency with the artisan’s tools of your choice: smith’s tools, brewer’s supplies, or mason’s tools.","builderInfo":{"mode":"CHOOSE_ONE","options":[{"amount":1,"category":"TOOL_TYPES","values":["smith"]},{"amount":1,"category":"TOOL_TYPES","values":["brewer"]},{"amount":1,"category":"TOOL_TYPES","values":["mason"]}]},"innate":{"proficiencies":[],"languages":[],"resistances":[],"saveAdvantages":[]}},{"id":"8wuL4K0viFBy1l9k","name":"Eye for Quality","img":"icons/tools/scribal/magnifying-glass.webp","description":"Whenever you make an ability check related to the origin of metalwork or masonry, you can add your PB to the roll. If you have Proficiency in a relevant skill or tool, you add double your PB to the roll.","builderInfo":{},"innate":{"proficiencies":[],"languages":[],"resistances":[],"saveAdvantages":[]}},{"id":"ETbhqzzPkqIf0e6G","name":"Languages","img":"icons/tools/scribal/ink-quill-pink.webp","description":"You know Trade and one additional language of your choice. Typical creatures of this heritage choose Dwarvish.","builderInfo":{"options":[{"amount":1,"category":"LANGUAGE_TYPES"}]},"innate":{"proficiencies":[],"languages":["trade"],"resistances":[],"saveAdvantages":[]}}],"description":"<p>Characters who choose this heritage were raised with the values and traditions of the Stone dwarven clans.</p><p>Regardless of time or circumstance, little changes in the great halls of the Stone dwarf clans. Above all else, the</p><p>residents of these ancient cities value tradition and champion the deeds of the ancestors who allowed their people to find safety within the earth. From infancy, the people of the Stone are instructed in the traditional dwarven arts of smithing, metalworking and masonry. Many happily devote their lives to mining and working precious metals beneath the surface of the world.</p><p>Though members of the Stone dwarf clans take great pride in their society, life in their cities is far from easy. The splendid caverns and mines occupied by the Stone dwarves are under constant attack by other subterrean denizens. As children are raised to wield a mining pick, they are also taught to wield the armaments of their people against the many enemies that seek to claim generations of dwarven treasures for themselves.</p>","alignment":"Choose one of the alignments approved by your GM. Typical creatures of this heritage tend towards Lawful or Good alignments."},"effects":[],"flags":{"exportSource":{"world":"black-flag","system":"black-flag","coreVersion":"11.292","systemVersion":"This is auto replaced"},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.zkaR4qWvWa97tRLo"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"black-flag","systemVersion":"This is auto replaced","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1675973694307,"modifiedTime":1676391804240,"lastModifiedBy":"HpJB4dX5ajFbAjnW"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"HpJB4dX5ajFbAjnW":3},"_id":"PjJoeVoeKZfboZec"}
{"name":"Grove","type":"heritage","img":"icons/environment/wilderness/terrain-forest-gray.webp","system":{"traits":[{"id":"VR0oRZVWwnJ6Udqc","name":"Beast Affinity","img":"icons/creatures/eyes/lizard-single-slit-blue.webp","description":"Using gestures and sounds, you can communicate simple ideas with beasts, and you have advantage on checks made to interact with non-hostile beasts.","builderInfo":{},"innate":{"proficiencies":[],"languages":[],"resistances":[],"saveAdvantages":[]}},{"id":"N126FA1k6iwe2Rkv","name":"Canopy Walker","img":"icons/magic/nature/root-vine-barrier-wall-brown.webp","description":"You have a climbing speed equal to your walking speed.","builderInfo":{},"innate":{"proficiencies":[],"languages":[],"resistances":[],"saveAdvantages":[]}},{"id":"RnnR4WkWnrndZKSQ","name":"Elf Weapon Training","img":"icons/skills/ranged/target-bullseye-arrow-yellow.webp","description":"You have Proficiency with the longsword, short sword, short bow, and longbow.","builderInfo":{},"innate":{"proficiencies":["longsword","shortsword","shortbow","longbow"],"languages":[],"resistances":[],"saveAdvantages":[]}},{"id":"GhskTH0VeTVvijwv","name":"Languages","img":"icons/tools/scribal/ink-quill-pink.webp","description":"You know Common and one additional languages of your choice. Typical creatures of this heritage choose Elvish.","builderInfo":{},"innate":{"proficiencies":[],"languages":["common"],"resistances":[],"saveAdvantages":[]}}],"alignment":"Choose one of the alignments approved by your GM. Typical creatures of this heritage tend towards Good or Neutral alignments.","description":"<p>Characters who chose this heritage were raised with the values and traditions of the grove elf communities.</p><p>When elves first walked the world, many chose to settle in the bounteous forests, drawn by the primordial music of the trees and beasts that dwelled among them. These early elves were the first grove elves, who established communities that intertwined harmoniously with the natural world—rather than seeking dominion over them. For ages, these communities have preserved the forests they call home, communing with nature in sacred groves, and taking up arms against those who dare to claim ownership of the land.</p><p>As time marches on and natural spaces are threatened by ever growing populations, all manner of creatures have come to share the values of the first grove elves. All whose hearts are open to the beasts and plants of the wild are welcome to settle among the people of the grove.</p>"},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.0mU8sYW0FFsPpiWh"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"black-flag","systemVersion":"This is auto replaced","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1676327219979,"modifiedTime":1676391802566,"lastModifiedBy":"HpJB4dX5ajFbAjnW"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"HpJB4dX5ajFbAjnW":3},"_id":"RpdUDbTvwKI0Ylxb"}
{"name":"Cloud","type":"heritage","img":"icons/magic/air/wind-tornado-funnel-blue-grey.webp","system":{"traits":[{"id":"dckmz9JJacX3I8ZH","name":"Touch of Magic","img":"icons/magic/light/orbs-firefly-hand-yellow.webp","description":"Choose a school of magic for which you have cultivated an affinity. You learn a cantrip of your choice from that school of magic. \nWhen you reach 3rd level, choose a 1st-level spell from that same school of magic, and when you reach 5th level, choose a 3rd-level spell from that same school. You learn these spells and can cast them at their lowest level. \nOnce you cast one of these spells, you must finish a long rest before you can cast that spell again using this feature. Your spellcasting ability for these spells is CHA, INT, or WIS (choose which during character creation).","builderInfo":{},"innate":{"proficiencies":[],"languages":[],"resistances":[],"saveAdvantages":[]}},{"id":"ZUX4kehfStxPze1n","name":"World of Wonders","img":"icons/magic/symbols/runes-triangle-orange-purple.webp","description":"You have Proficiency in the Arcana skill.","builderInfo":{},"innate":{"proficiencies":["arcana"],"languages":[],"resistances":[],"saveAdvantages":[]}},{"id":"vTQk8OxQaABSqCcM","name":"Languages","img":"icons/tools/scribal/ink-quill-pink.webp","description":"You know Common and two additional languages of your choice. Typical creatures of this heritage choose Elvish and Draconic.","builderInfo":{},"innate":{"proficiencies":[],"languages":["common"],"resistances":[],"saveAdvantages":[]}}],"alignment":"Choose one of the alignments approved by your GM. Typical creatures of this heritage tend towards Lawful or Neutral alignments. ","description":"<p>Characters who choose this heritage were raised with the values and traditions of the Cloud Elf communities.</p><p>Many accounts concerning the origins of the elves have been spun, and almost all are deeply intertwined with tales of magic. In a time long lost to memory, a group of elves clung fast to these tales and named themselves mages, stewards of the magical forces that coursed through the cosmos. These elves were the first of the cloud elf tribes and the towers they built to study the mysteries of the skies eventually became the heart of thriving cities.</p><p>Though many elves still dwell within these towering cities, striving for an ever greater understanding of magic, people from all over the world have been drawn into these cloud communities—eager to study the arcane arts at the finest magic academies or simply to dwell among kindred spirits for whom magic is the center of their world.</p>"},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.XLbdQNEMaffSI0aM"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"black-flag","systemVersion":"This is auto replaced","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1676327219979,"modifiedTime":1676391799558,"lastModifiedBy":"HpJB4dX5ajFbAjnW"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"HpJB4dX5ajFbAjnW":3},"_id":"iZtCLR28GFbul7Gc"}
{"name":"Fireforge","type":"heritage","img":"icons/magic/fire/elemental-fire-flying.webp","system":{"traits":[{"id":"gh95TrxKhL6ozTEB","name":"Dwarven Weapon Training","img":"icons/skills/melee/hand-grip-axe-strike-orange.webp","description":"You have Proficiency with the battleaxe, handaxe, light hammer, and warhammer.","builderInfo":{},"innate":{"proficiencies":["battleaxe","handaxe","lightHammer","warhammer"],"languages":[],"resistances":[],"saveAdvantages":[]},"source":"Fireforge","sourceId":"RXLPdpF8JIxVOENJ"},{"id":"KejDTP4TVdDf3CWZ","name":"Expert Artisan","img":"icons/skills/trades/smithing-smelter-tongs.webp","description":"You gain Proficiency with glassblower’s tools or smith’s tools. Choose one of those tools. Your PB is doubled for any ability check you make that uses the chosen tool.","builderInfo":{},"innate":{"proficiencies":[],"languages":[],"resistances":[],"saveAdvantages":[]},"source":"Fireforge","sourceId":"RXLPdpF8JIxVOENJ"},{"id":"GZtErx8TUd0rusx6","name":"Forgecraft","img":"icons/magic/defensive/shield-barrier-flaming-diamond-orange.webp","description":"You are resistant to fire damage.","builderInfo":{},"innate":{"proficiencies":[],"languages":[],"resistances":["fire"],"saveAdvantages":[]},"source":"Fireforge","sourceId":"RXLPdpF8JIxVOENJ"},{"id":"AOgNqJ8XF59nWyW5","name":"Friend to Elementals","img":"icons/magic/fire/elemental-fire-flying.webp","description":"You can speak, read, and write Ignan in addition to your chosen languages.","builderInfo":{},"innate":{"proficiencies":[],"languages":["ignan"],"resistances":[],"saveAdvantages":[]}},{"id":"nroQycUtHEPZyozE","name":"Reforge","img":"icons/skills/melee/sword-damaged-broken-blue.webp","description":"Your people have a deep connection with elemental fire and have collectively learned how to repair forged items with a touch. You know the mending cantrip, and you can cast it as an action. However, you can use this trait to repair objects made only of metal, such as reconnecting two halves of a broken sword.","builderInfo":{},"innate":{"proficiencies":[],"languages":[],"resistances":[],"saveAdvantages":[]}},{"id":"w9fje9t0CRmp9Fmb","name":"Languages","img":"icons/tools/scribal/ink-quill-pink.webp","description":"You know Trade and one additional language of your choice. Typical creatures of this heritage choose Dwarvish.","builderInfo":{"options":[{"amount":1,"category":"LANGUAGE_TYPES"}]},"innate":{"proficiencies":{"0":"0","1":"[object Object]","length":2,"prevObject":{"0":{},"1":{},"length":2,"prevObject":{"0":{"jQuery361090241225240335381":{"display":""}},"length":1}}},"languages":{"0":"trade","1":"1","2":"[object Object]","length":3,"prevObject":{"0":{},"1":{},"2":{},"length":3,"prevObject":{"0":{"jQuery361090241225240335381":{"display":""}},"length":1}}},"resistances":{"0":"0","1":"[object Object]","length":2,"prevObject":{"0":{},"1":{},"length":2,"prevObject":{"0":{"jQuery361090241225240335381":{"display":""}},"length":1}}},"saveAdvantages":{"0":"0","1":"[object Object]","length":2,"prevObject":{"0":{},"1":{},"length":2,"prevObject":{"0":{"jQuery361090241225240335381":{"display":""}},"length":1}}}},"source":"Fireforge","sourceId":"RXLPdpF8JIxVOENJ"}],"description":"<p>Characters who choose this heritage were raised with the values and traditions of the Fireforge dwarven clans.</p><p>Dwarven legends state the best metal-crafting is done in the fires of the earth itself. Long ago, groups of dwarves that followed this tradition settled near areas of volcanic activity, turning such places into their forges. These dwarves were the founders of the Fireforge clans. To this day, these communities toil in the heat of magma, creating weapons, armor, and other goods noteworthy even among the finest dwarven crafts. They trade these goods for necessities not found in the harsh environment of their chosen settlements.</p><p>Fireforge communities maintain good relations with elemental creatures, coming to their aid when needed. In return, these elementals assist